data.name: resultSize
data.description: The maximum number of drills (or courses) to include in the result. If not specified, the results for all (remaining) drills are returned.

data.name: resultStart
data.description: The index number (zero-based) of the first drill (or course) to include in the result. Use this parameter, in combination with resultSize, to apply pagination of the result; it will limit the number of drills included in the result. Defaults to 0.

data.name: searchField
data.description: Specifies which fields will be searched. Can be included multiple times to specify multiple search fields. If not specified, all available fields will be searched.
Search the Drill Store for available drills and courses.

response.name: Drillables
response.description: Contains a list of drills and courses (with their associated drills).

data.name: Search in Drill Store
query
data.description: The text to search for. It can be a single word, or multiple words (separated with a space). The search is case-insensitive. If multiple words are specified, the default search behavior is to search for any of the words. The AND operator can be used to search for all words, e.g. "milk AND butter". Note that the AND operator must be in capitals.

data.name: resultSize
data.description: The maximum number of drills (or courses) to include in the result. If not specified, the results for all (remaining) drills are returned.

data.name: resultStart
data.description: The index number (zero-based) of the first drill (or course) to include in the result. Use this parameter, in combination with resultSize, to apply pagination of the result; it will limit the number of drills included in the result. Defaults to 0.

data.name: searchField
data.description: Specifies which fields will be searched. Can be included multiple times to specify multiple search fields. If not specified, all available fields will be searched. Possible values are:  NAME, DESCRIPTION, SUBJECT, TAGS, CONTENTS.

data.name: sortDirection
data.description: The sort direction (ascending or descending), if a sortField has been specified. If omitted, a default sort direction is used, which depends on the sortField. Possible values are: ASC, DESC.

data.name: sortField
data.description: The field to sort the result by.

Drillster is an open cloud based memorization platform that helps users learn more in less time. Use our API to integrate with Drillster or to create your own memorization solution.

For detailed information about this API, please refer to http://www.drillster.com/info/api-2/.
